pullRequest.body:
In this PR, it is shown that if `W : MorphismProperty C` has a left calculus of fractions and `C` is preadditive, then the localized category is also preadditive.

Is this a useful simp-lemma?
```suggestion
@[simp]
lemma symm_add : Ï†.symm.add = Ï†.add := by
```

I think it makes sense to wrap this whole `neg'` and `add'` section into a `section implementation_details` with a little comment saying that the whole section should never be used directly, but is only there to set up the group structure on the hom-sets.
